a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Why do I get this ?</span><hr size=1> Dam/Del, Lev, DamBon, PriModal, ComPriModal<br>8/20, 40, 5, 21, 1.050<br>11/25, 40, 5, 27, 1.080<br><br>PriModal = (2*Dam)+DamBon<br>ComPriModal = PriModal/Del<br><br>Hmm....<br><br>Personally I carried this on and worked out, from the above, dps using:-<br>Primary Hand: ComPriModal + chance to DA<br>Secondary Hand: ComOffModal + chance to DW + chance to DA.<br><br>At 40:-<br>FB = 15.834 DPS Primary 8.807 DPS Off<br>CoT = 16.286 DPS Primary 9.687 DPS Off<br><br>Anyone know how this compares to RL results ?<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ueveel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eveel</A> at: 1/23/02 4:19:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ujdahlin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jdahlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(1/23/02 10:22:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=474.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do I get this ?</span><hr size=1> Hmmm... haven't found a DPS formula yet... can someone post a link to it?  Thanks.<br><br>IMHO, the only valuae of DPS calcs is when disscussing damage output with someone and is an unneccessary step in figuring out which weapon to weild in which hand.  After all, once you have the Comparable Modals you already know which wepaons do more damage.  Converting this into DPS gains yuou nothing except, perhaps, common ground to talk to warriors about if you want to compare a CoT vs a Centi Long Sword. <br><br>BTW, a slight typo in eveels post:<br>&quot;Primary Hand: ComPriModal + chance to DA&quot;<br>and<br>&quot;Secondary Hand: ComOffModal + chance to DW + chance to DA.&quot;<br><br>should be <br>&quot;Primary Hand: ComPriModal * 1.&lt;chance to DA&gt;&quot;<br>and<br>&quot;Secondary Hand: ComOffModal * 1.&lt;chance to DW&gt; * 1.chance to DA&gt;&quot;<br><br>you never &quot;add&quot; percentages, you multiply them  If my PriMod is 1.080 and my DA percentage is 41%, then my comparable modal is 1.080*(1+0.41) = 1.448  which is not the same as 1.080 + .41 = 1.49.<br><br>Suppose you average damage with a weapon (basically PriMod) was 3.000 and DA was 50%... would your &quot;average damage&quot; with that weapon now be 3.5 or 4.5?  It would be 4.5 because, on average, in 2 checks, you will swing it 3 times (1 time only once, 1 time you will DA).<br><br> <p>Happy hunting and safe travels,Ishinru</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ueveel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eveel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(1/24/02 10:52:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=474.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do I get this ?</span><hr size=1> Aye, my wording was wrong should have been:-<br><br>Primaryhand: ComPriModal + &quot;Damage done due to DA on average&quot;<br>Offhand: ComOffModal + &quot;Damage done due to DA, on average, given the likelihood of a DA on a DW&quot;<br><br>Bah, someone check my maths please, I'm not a very good explainer of how I get to an answer <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Primaryhand:-<br>(((((2*Damage)+Damage Bonus)/Delay)*10)+(((((2*Damage)+Damage Bonus)/Delay)*10)*DA))<br><br>Offhand:-<br>(((((2*Damage)/Delay)*DW)*10)+(((((2*Damage)/Delay)*DWSa)*10)*DA))<br><br>Where:-<br>DA=  likelihood of Double Attack happening<br>DW= likelihood of Dual Wield Happening <br><br>Of course what I did forget to take into account is likelihood of actually hitting <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>For pure DPS tho, remember that this doesn't take into account any variations in strength - which, admittedly, mostly affects special attacks - and assume's most of the damage takes place around the Modal (Weapon Damage * 2) + Damage Bonus. <br>This, as has been stated, is just the sort of thing you need when comparing weapons but if you want actual, real world, DPS then the &quot;only&quot; way to get a realistic result is to parse. Even this can produce un-realistic results. Parse a weapon against low blue mobs and you'll get a much higher DPS than you would against high red ones.<br><br>To be honest though, due to VI's RNG nearly all results will be unique and should only be used as estimates, not fact.<br>The quotes &quot;Yesterday I fought mob X and got Y DPS&quot; and &quot;Today I fought mob X and got Z DPS&quot; made by the same person with the same level/gear/buffs and weapons are *not*contradictory in this instance. <br>The RNG allows for a differentiation in results and it's not until you have enough evidence to say that the RNG varies DPS by X% that you can start applying formulas to weapons to get the true DPS.<br><br><br>Damn, 2 things spring to mind - 1st is that I spend too much time thinking about how EQ probably works - 2nd is that I flunked maths <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=474.topic&start=21&sto